      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Operational Considerations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Rate limiting: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "a swarm of 50 workers can saturate the Anthropic API in seconds. Use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "asyncio.Semaphore(max_concurrent)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " or a token-bucket limiter inside the worker factory."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Idempotency: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "if a worker crashes mid-task, the task will be re-claimed by another worker. Make tasks idempotent \u2014 the same task run twice should produce the same result without side effects."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Cost monitoring: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "homogeneous workers using the same model make cost estimation easy \u2014 multiply task count \u00d7 average tokens per task \u00d7 model price per token."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Worker count vs. task volume: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "adding more workers helps throughput only up to the API's concurrency limit. For LLM-based swarms, 8\u201316 concurrent workers is usually the practical ceiling."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Swarm agents are homogeneous workers that follow a single local rule \u2014 poll, claim, execute, push \u2014 with no central controller."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "In LangGraph, use the "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Send"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " API to fan out tasks concurrently; use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Annotated[list, operator.add]"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " so all workers can push results without overwriting each other."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "For dynamic workloads, replace the Send fan-out with an "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "asyncio.Queue"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " polling loop \u2014 faster workers automatically pick up more tasks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Handle failures by collecting failed task IDs from the result pool and re-queuing them for retry with a stronger model before declaring the swarm done."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Choose swarm over manager-worker when task volume is high and unknown at compile time; choose orchestrator or blackboard when tasks are interdependent."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
